    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create new requirements for dogs held under dangerous dogs legislation",
        "additional_details": "Currently there is no guidance from Government or specific legal requirements for owners to be informed when a dog - that is being held under dangerous dogs legislation - is sick, needs vet treatment or died. Owners can also struggle to get copies of vet and kennel records.",
        "background": "We want new legal requirements in relation to dogs that are being held under dangerous dogs law. Authorities should immediately notify owners if their dog is unwell, needs a vet, is dying or died. And no dog's body to be cremated or frozen without an owner\u2019s consent, so they can seek a post mortem.",
